text.section:
In this section, "normal repairs and maintenance":
means an expenditure to replace original components of a building to maintain the physical character of the building in its current condition; and
includes:
interior or exterior painting;
landscaping;
fencing;
replacing gutters or downspouts;
adding storm windows, storm doors, or weatherstripping;
adding insulation;
electric rewiring;
replacing plumbing and light fixtures;
replacing a furnace with more efficient oil or gas burners;
redecorating;
installing new ceilings or wall surfaces;
removing room partitions to change the shape of a room;
replacing a roof with a roof of a similar type and material;
replacing an existing driveway and lead walk;
repairing a foundation because of structural defect or age if there is no enlargement of the improvement or building; and
replacing an existing air conditioner or other built-in appliance.
